                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 841.731/628</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Great Britain</hi> (<persName
                        corresp="#p_PWH1" type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Page</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-06-17T17:00:00+00:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 17, 1915, 5 p. m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received 7 p. m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>2310. Your 1715, June 15, 9 p. m. Am informed at Foreign Office that British
                    Government has refused definitely to give consent to Netherlands Oversea Trust
                    plan for transmission of cables.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">American Ambassador</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
